condition:  (1) in every transition t where x is assigned, y is also  
assigned and (2) every assignment of y can be represented in the form  
f(ax+b)
action: in every expression e such that y is in support(e) replace y  
with f(ax+b)

ok, i think the "form" needs some work.

p1 -> {}[1,1]<x:=1,y:=2> -> p2 -> {}[1,1]<x:=7, y:=14>-> p3 -> {} 
[1,1]<z:=y>

becomes

p1 -> {}[1,1]<x:=1,y:=2> -> p2 -> {}[1,1]<x:=7, y:=14>-> p3 -> {} 
[1,1]<z:=2*x>

"f(x)" could also be something like \neg x

